PN,44705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1778519160
OL,3,C'Voice for the voiceless': How Agnes
OL,4,CLunny is transforming disability
OL,5,Csupport
OL,7,FI ask Agnes what she would change
OL,8,Fabout the current social care system.
OL,9,FAs well as earlier intervention,
OL,10,Fresources and a lack of multi year
OL,11,Fbudget means the system is operating
OL,12,F'hand to mouth.' But she's keen to
OL,13,Femphasise that improvement doesn't
OL,14,Falways cost money. Just acknowledging
OL,15,Fthose with learning disabilities.
OL,16,FKeeping them in our communities and
OL,17,Fkeeping them in vision can make a
OL,18,Fdifference to acceptance and
OL,19,Fappreciation of those individuals.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
